<section xml:id="_understanding_the_directory_structure">
<title>Understanding the Directory Structure</title>
<informaltable frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1">
<tgroup cols="2">
<colspec colname="col_1" colwidth="50*"/>
<colspec colname="col_2" colwidth="50*"/>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry align="left" valign="top"><simpara>Folder Name</simpara></entry>
<entry align="left" valign="top"><simpara>Description</simpara></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry align="left" valign="top"><simpara>bin</simpara></entry>
<entry align="left" valign="top"><simpara>This folder contains shell scripts that you need to install and setup. You will also see a file called all_in_one.sh , and this is the file that you would execute to compile the asciidoc into various file formats, and save them in the "docs" folder. You shouldn&#8217;t be editing any files in this folder.</simpara></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry align="left" valign="top"><simpara>build</simpara></entry>
<entry align="left" valign="top"><simpara>This is a temporary folder that gets deleted and re-created every time we "compile" the documentation. You shouldn&#8217;t need to mess with files in this folder.</simpara></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry align="left" valign="top"><simpara>content</simpara></entry>
<entry align="left" valign="top"><simpara>This is where you will be contributing by editing the files in this folder.</simpara></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry align="left" valign="top"><simpara>docs</simpara></entry>
<entry align="left" valign="top"><simpara>You shouldn&#8217;t need to edit any files in this folder. But you are welcome to open the files in this folder to check the "compiled output" of your changes , to ensure they are correct before pushing your code to the github, and request for your branch to be merged with the "main" branch in github.</simpara></entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</informaltable>
